Global Funds Buy Net 6.11 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-04-29T04:36:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/global-funds-buy-net-6-11-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 6.11
billion rupees ($137 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, declined 26 percent to 800.4 billion rupees, or 41
percent of the gross market position on the last day of trading
in contracts for April, according to the exchangeâ€™s website.
Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 8.33 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
